@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>PureWave | Privacy Policy</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="PureWave privacy policy — what data is collected when you visit this site, why it is collected, and how to opt out." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="page-intro">
    <span class="section-tag">Privacy</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
        PureWave takes a straightforward approach to privacy: collect only what is needed to understand how the site is used,
        be transparent about it, and give visitors a way to opt out. This policy covers what data is collected when you visit
        <strong>purewaveacoustic.co.za</strong>, why it is collected, and what you can do about it.
    </p>
    <p class="privacy-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
    <div class="privacy-body">

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Who is responsible for your data</h2>
            <p>
                PureWave Home Theatre Consultancy, operated by Danie Barnardo, Durban, South Africa.<br />
                Contact: <a href="mailto:purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za">purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za</a>
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>What is collected and why</h2>
            <p>
                This site uses <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> to understand how visitors interact with it — which pages are visited,
                how long people stay, and what devices and general locations they come from. No names, email addresses, or personal
                identifiers are sent to Google Analytics unless you submit the intake form.
            </p>
            <p>Google Analytics collects:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Pages visited and time spent on each</li>
                <li>General location at city level (derived from IP address — the IP itself is not stored by Google)</li>
                <li>Device type, browser, and operating system</li>
                <li>How you arrived at the site (direct, search, referral)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This information is used solely to improve the site — understanding which pages are useful and which are confusing,
                and whether the site works properly on different devices.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Intake form data</h2>
            <p>
                If you submit the intake questionnaire, the information you provide (name, contact details, room details, and preferences)
                is stored securely and used only to respond to your enquiry. It is not shared with third parties, sold, or used for
                advertising. You can request deletion of your intake submission at any time by contacting
                <a href="mailto:purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za">purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za</a>.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Legal basis for processing</h2>
            <p>
                PureWave operates under the <strong>Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA)</strong>, South Africa's data protection law.
                Analytics data is processed on the basis of legitimate interest — understanding how the site performs so it can be improved.
                Intake form data is processed to fulfil your request for a consultation.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Data retention</h2>
            <p>
                Google Analytics data is retained for <strong>14 months</strong> (Google's default), after which it is automatically deleted.
                Intake form submissions are retained for as long as the business relationship is active, or up to 3 years, whichever is shorter.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Google's role</h2>
            <p>
                Google acts as a data processor for analytics data collected on this site. Their data practices are governed by
                <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
                PureWave does not share your data with Google beyond what Google Analytics collects automatically via the tracking tag.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Your rights under POPIA</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Know what personal information PureWave holds about you</li>
                <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
                <li>Request deletion of your information</li>
                <li>Object to processing of your information</li>
                <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                To exercise any of these rights, contact <a href="mailto:purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za">purewave@purewaveacoustic.co.za</a>.
                Requests are handled within 30 days.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>How to opt out of analytics tracking</h2>
            <p>You can prevent Google Analytics from collecting data about your visit in two ways:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>
                    — works in all major desktop browsers.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Use a browser with tracking protection enabled, or a browser extension that blocks analytics scripts (such as uBlock Origin).
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
            <p>
                If this policy changes in a material way, the updated date at the top of this page will reflect the change.
                Continued use of the site after a policy update constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>
